Lachowski May Apply For CEO’s Post at Poland’s PKO, Rp.pl Says

-- B y   D a v i d   M c Q u a i d
-- 
2011-02-11T06:26:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-11/lachowski-may-apply-for-ceo-s-post-at-poland-s-pko-rp-pl-says.html
Slawomir Lachowski, the former chief
executive officer of BRE Bank SA, plans to apply for the post of
CEO at PKO Bank Polski SA, Poland’s largest lender,
 Rzeczpospolita  reported today, citing a person involved in the
selection process whom it didn’t name.  Lachowski would be competing against Zbigniew Jagiello,
PKO’s incumbent CEO, who said he will apply for a second term,
the newspaper reported on its Rp.pl website. The deadline for
candidates to submit their applications to PKO’s supervisory
board is Feb. 16, Rp.pl said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
